@suquark 
Regarding `__qualname__ may be better for python3.3+`: 
the purpose of this PR is to replace function id with function descriptor in task info structure. For Python , a function descriptor is a list of these strings `module_name, function_name, class_name, and optionally hash of source code`. With function descriptor, we can load a function from local disk, without having to store every function in GCS. Thus, the `function_name` here must be the short name, without class name. (While `__qualname__` contains the class name, and doesn't work for python 2.)

Regarding `is there any reason that we have to introduce function_class`:
@guoyuhong This parameter isn't used. I think we should either remove this parameter, or make `actor.py` use this `from_function` function.

