If `IsMacDataFlagSet` is true, this message would be accounted as a mac data frame. `VerifyOrExit(!mSeriesFlags.IsMacDataFlagSet());` is used to avoid duplication.

For example, when `IsMacDataFlagSet` is `true` and we receive a Link Probe message. The Link Probe message would be accounted first at `AggregateLinkMetrics` in `Mac::HandleReceivedFrame` because it is itself a link layer data frame. And then accounted again at `AggregateLinkMetrics` in `Mle::HandleLinkProbe`. I did this because Link Probe are not link layer messages so I cannot directly count it in Mac. If `IsMacDataFlagSet` is true, Link Probe would be accounted in Mac layer and won't be accounted in Mle. If `IsMacDataFlagSet` is false and `IsLinkProbeFlagSet()` is `true`, Link Probe would be accounted in Mle.

